<s-title>
Meuse river data set
</s-title>

<s-description>
This data set gives locations and top soil heavy metal concentrations
(ppm), along with a number of soil and landscape variables, collected in
a flood plain of the river Meuse, near the village Stein. Heavy metal
concentrations are bulk sampled from an area of approximately 15 m
x 15 m.
</s-description>

<s-usage>
<s-old-style-usage>
data(meuse)
</s-old-style-usage>
</s-usage>

<s-section name="FORMAT">
This data frame contains the following columns:
<descrip>
<tag/Sample/original sample number
<tag/x/a numeric vector; x-coordinate (m)
in RDM (Dutch topographical map coordinates) 
<tag/y/a numeric vector; y-coordinate (m)
in RDM (Dutch topographical map coordinates)
<tag/cadmium/topsoil cadmium concentration, ppm.; note that zero cadmium
values in the original data set have been shifted to 0.2 (half the lowest 
non-zero value) 
<tag/copper/topsoil copper concentration, ppm. 
<tag/lead/topsoil lead concentration, ppm. 
<tag/zinc/topsoil zinc concentration, ppm.  
<tag/elev/relative elevation
<tag/dist/distance to river Meuse (m)
<tag/om/organic matter, as percentage 
<tag/ffreq/flooding frequency class
<tag/soil/soil type
<tag/lime/lime class
<tag/landuse/landuse class
</descrip>

</s-section>

